   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1833_05_09_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Personography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworth Town<lb/></placeName>
                  <date when="1833-05-09">May <unclear>9</unclear> <hi rend="superscript">h</hi>. 1833</date><lb/></dateline>
               <salute><choice><orig>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.</orig><reg>Dear</reg></choice> Sir<lb/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p><persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2" cert="high">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. <choice><orig>E.</orig><reg>Edgeworth</reg></choice></persName> Perceiving that an essential <choice><orig>charac<lb/>
               teristic</orig><reg>characteristic</reg></choice> of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Garry1">a chimney sweeper</title> - <hi rend="underline">his brush</hi><lb/>
               was omitted in the drawing we sent<lb/>
               you now sends a sketch which you<lb/>
               must <del>show</del> <add>give</add> the engraver when<lb/>
               you put the little drawing in his<lb/>
               hands - It is merely to show that<lb/>
               the boy must have brush in hand<lb/>
               - the first drawing sent, is to be followed<lb/>
               in all other respects -<lb/></p>
               <p>You will be so good to send<lb/>
                  us <title ref="./Workography.xml#">a proof</title> <del><unclear></unclear></del> <hi rend="underline">for correction</hi><lb/>
               - Enclose to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#GosseW1">Sir William Gosset</persName><lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Castle-Dublin_IE">Castle Dublin</placeName> -<lb/></p>
               <p>I am much obliged by your having sent for<lb/>
               me <persName ref="./Personography.xml#McInJ1">Sir James M<hi rend="superscript">c</hi>.Intosh</persName>'s discourse on <choice><orig>Meta<lb/>
                  physics</orig><reg>Metaphysics</reg></choice> to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#North-Audley-Street-1_ENK">North Audley Street</placeName><lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1833_05_09_page02.jpg"/>
               I have sent your message to the <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MarcJ1">author</persName><lb/>
               of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Berth1">Bertha</title> and an answer will be<lb/>
               sent to you I am sure punctually<lb/></p>
               <p>She does not reside with us, but<lb/>
               is a friend &amp; near connexion for<lb/>
               whom we have the highest esteem &amp;<lb/>
               greatest interest - I rejoice that <title ref="./Workography.xml#Berth1"><choice><orig>Ber<lb/>
               tha</orig><reg>Bertha</reg></choice></title> has succeeded so well &amp; that<lb/>
               you desire more by the same hand,<lb/>
               &amp; <unclear></unclear> young people - I wish your son<lb/>
               success in that line which I think<lb/>
               he is wise to pursue as it is likely to<lb/>
               last better than <add>the</add> more fancy line of litera<lb/>
               ture that must be subject to the changes<lb/>
               of fashion politics &amp;c - But as long<lb/>
               as people have children <del><unclear></unclear></del> and<lb/>
               any sense &amp; any money they must<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1833_05_09_page03.jpg"/>
               have books for them &amp; the best will infallibly<lb/>
               make their way best <add>&amp; last longer</add> because <unclear>put</unclear> to the<lb/>
               proof constantly<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               I am <choice><orig>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></orig><reg>Dear</reg></choice> Sir<lb/>
               Yours truly<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/></closer>
            <postscript><p>Be so good as to send the letter<lb/>
               enclosed by the <choice><orig>Gen<hi rend="superscript">l</hi>.</orig><reg>General</reg></choice> Post the<lb/>
               day you receive this packet<lb/></p></postscript>
         </div>
